                            <comment id="13837560" author="tharindu_rusira" created="Tue, 3 Dec 2013 10:42:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=dweiss&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;dweiss&quot;&gt;Dawid Weiss&lt;/a&gt;, I&apos;m currently working on this issue and for the time being I attach a simple implementation of the final step of murmurhash3 as you suggested. &lt;br/&gt;
Your feedback is highly appreciated.&lt;br/&gt;
Thanks.&lt;br/&gt;
P.S. not tested&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13837569" author="dweiss" created="Tue, 3 Dec 2013 10:54:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You introduced an unused import (Random). And the code could be simplified a bit too (although it remains identical at the bytecode level it seems clearer):&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
    /**
     * Hashes a 4-&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;byte&lt;/span&gt; sequence (Java &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;).
     */
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;static&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; hash(&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; k) {
        k ^= k &amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt; 16;
        k *= 0x85ebca6b;
        k ^= k &amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt; 13;
        k *= 0xc2b2ae35;
        k ^= k &amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt; 16;
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; k;
    }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13837592" author="tharindu_rusira" created="Tue, 3 Dec 2013 11:27:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=dweiss&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;dweiss&quot;&gt;Dawid Weiss&lt;/a&gt; for the quick feedback. I&apos;m attaching the reworked patch.&lt;br/&gt;
By the way, any ideas of a better hash mechanism you can think of (which suits this context)? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13837610" author="dweiss" created="Tue, 3 Dec 2013 11:52:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m not an expert on hash functions, really. I believe Austin Appleby&apos;s did a good job on MH3 and I rely on his work here.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
